{
  "texts": [
    "The baseline pruning strategies employed low-level pruning techniques, targeting the removal of only 20% of the connections.",
    "We chose low-level pruning as it is the most widely used approach that does not affect much on the pre-training loss [26].",
    "We fine-tune a separate model on SST2 and COLA tasks for three epochs and try four learning rates: [2, 3, 4, 5] × 10-5.",
    "The best evaluation accuracies are averaged and the most suitable hyperparameters for each pruned model.",
    "We observed that pruning 20% of the attention heads speeds up fine-tuning by more than 22% and reduces the memory overhead per instance by around 18%."
  ]
}